> Subject: hehr windows
> Message-ID: <064c01c9f8d1$ac3caa40$04b5fec0$(-at-)net>
>
> After some exhaustive searching for window glass, I have come down to
> laminated glass. I know a lot of you recommended tempered, but to get
> tempered with UV block was quite expensive.
>
> The laminate should last at least 40 years, as my original side window
glass
> is laminate. It is in ok condition, there is some de-laminating, but it is
> minimal and it is hidden. Not bad for 40-45 years old.
>
> The new glass will block 95% UV rays.
>
> My glass guy has recommended using urethane adhesive instead of butyl. He
> says he is not longer allowed to use butyl tape on windshields, and says
> that the urethane will absorb the vibrations etc. This will negate the need
> for a gasket between the glass and the frame. I like the look of the
gasket,
> so I may still use it, but I'm not sure if it will fit. He suggests I just
> lay a fat bead of urethane on the frame, push the glass in. Let it sit
> overnight or 48 hours. Then flip the frame over, and cut the excess
urethane
> out.
>
> I should be getting the glass in a couple days, and I'll let you know how
it
> goes.
>
> -Kevin
>
> '65 kombi
> '69 single cab
> Jamaica Plain, MA
